<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,416,222,248]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Biology and notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shannon &amp; Aubertin" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[422,676,222,248]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Valdiviomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis box="[422,676,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Valdiviomyia edwardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with native forests. 
<emphasis box="[1045,1273,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Systema Dipterorum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thompson, F. C. &amp; Pape, T" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" refId="ref141080" refString="Thompson, F. C. &amp; Pape, T (2010) Systema Dipterorum. http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 20 May 2018)" type="url" year="2010">Thompson &amp; Pape 2010</bibRefCitation>
) only describes this species distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[749,863,258,284]" name="Argentina" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, however, 
<bibRefCitation author="Etcheverry, M." box="[983,1187,258,285]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref127618" refString="Etcheverry, M. (1963) Descripciones originales, sinonimia y distribucion geografica de las especies de la familia Syrphidae (Diptera) en Chile. Publicaciones del Centro de Estudios Entomologicos, 5, 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1963">Etcheverry (1963)</bibRefCitation>
determined that it can also be found in 
<collectingCountry box="[339,403,294,320]" name="Chile" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Chile</collectingCountry>
. Thus, this species has been reclassified as native to 
<collectingCountry box="[993,1104,294,320]" name="Argentina" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1160,1224,294,320]" name="Chile" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Chile</collectingCountry>
. All biological and ecological aspects of this species are unknown.
</paragraph>
